  "text": "HomeShoppingIt also offers powerful \"nutraceutical\" supplements and a serum-and-cream duo promising younger-looking skin.Photo: Courtesy of LymaBrand Bio is Fashionista's guide to the best independent fashion and beauty brands — a resource for retailers, job seekers, B2B companies and consumers alike. If you'd like your brand to be featured, fill out this form.LymaHeadquarters: London, U.K.E-commerce: lyma.life/en-usSocial Media: Instagram / FacebookWhat: A luxury skin-care brand addressing signs of aging through clinic-grade cold laser technology, nutraceutical supplements and youth-boosting skin products.Price Range: $53-$2,695Founder: Lucy GoffOrigin Story: In 2012, when Lucy Goff was in the hospital battling septicemia, she tried a cocktail of drugs and supplements, and none of them worked. She then met Dr. Paul Clayton, a world authority on preventative degenerative disease, and he prescribed her a new protocol using peer-reviewed, patented ingredients and she made a full recovery. Goff and Dr. Clayton set out to connect with the best scientists in the world with one aim in mind: to produce the ultimate all-in-one supplement. Lyma was born in 2018 with a goal to produce \"a proven formula, using peer-reviewed ingredients and powerful enough to unlock human potential.\"Scroll to ContinueRecommended ArticlesTaking an evidence-based nutrition approach to formulation, Lyma uses validated ingredients that cannot be found in effective doses through food, each dosed at active levels and proven in peer-reviewed studies to offer the highest grade of pharmaconutrition. Lyma's supplements are infused with a smart-technology delivery system to overcome limitations posed in their organic form and deliver health and beauty benefits.Stockists: Dermstore, Goop, Revolve, Bergdorf Goodman, Neiman Marcus, Joanna Czech, Moda Operandi, HarrodsHero Products: Lyma Laser Starter Kit Bundle ($2,695), The Lyma Supplement ($269), Skin Care Serum and Cream ($655)PR Representa